## Vendoring for Air-Gapped Labs

Many CAC investigative environments are air-gapped or operate under restrictive network policies. Your tool SHOULD function offline. Vendor all ontology assets locally:

- CASE / UCO ontology files under `vendor/ontologies/case-uco/<version>/`
- CAC Ontology files under `vendor/ontologies/cac/<version>/`
- SOLVE-IT ontology TTLs under `vendor/ontologies/solve-it/<version>/`
- The `case_validate` tool shipped alongside (or pinned in `requirements.txt`)
- CI checks vendored versions against upstream to detect drift

Air-gapped deployments MUST NOT require network access for SHACL validation, technique lookup, or `case_validate`.
